nurture our biome by

00:52:35.210 --> 00:52:37.920
eating these correct foods.

00:52:37.920 --> 00:52:40.600
But there are some instances
in my practice where I have

00:52:40.600 --> 00:52:43.220
referred patients for
fecal transplant.

00:52:43.220 --> 00:52:46.150
But those are people who are
really, really ill and where

00:52:46.150 --> 00:52:48.220
all these other things
haven't worked.

00:52:48.220 --> 00:52:51.580
And the next question is, where
did they get the healthy

00:52:51.580 --> 00:52:52.330
feces from?

00:52:52.330 --> 00:52:55.080
They usually get it from a
parent or a family member,

00:52:55.080 --> 00:52:56.790
someone who shares
the candlesticks

00:52:56.790 --> 00:53:00.010
with them, as well.

00:53:00.010 --> 00:53:04.220
But it's kind of a last-ditch
solution.

00:53:04.220 --> 00:53:07.650
And another question that I get
a lot is, how about those

00:53:07.650 --> 00:53:10.460
over-the-counter supplements,
those probiotics?

00:53:10.460 --> 00:53:13.500
And even people like Justin
Sonnenburg, what they're

00:53:13.500 --> 00:53:16.580
really doing is trying to mine
all this information to come

00:53:16.580 --> 00:53:18.080
up with the ideal probiotic.

00:53:18.080 --> 00:53:20.160
Because that's where
the biotech is.

00:53:20.160 --> 00:53:22.390
That's where the money
is, right?

00:53:22.390 --> 00:53:25.000
What I'm talking about, eating
vegetables and getting to know

00:53:25.000 --> 00:53:27.350
the soil, I'm never going
to get rich on this.

00:53:32.500 --> 00:53:38.280
But the problem with probiotics
is, because just as

00:53:38.280 --> 00:53:41.600
I was talking about, a lot of
our microbiome is inherited.

00:53:41.600 --> 00:53:44.250
So yours might look very
different than the gentleman

00:53:44.250 --> 00:53:48.120
in the red shirt behind you
and maybe different from

00:53:48.120 --> 00:53:50.380
someone in the checkered
shirt here.

00:53:50.380 --> 00:53:53.010
And so what is the
ideal microbiome?

00:53:53.010 --> 00:53:53.990
We don't know.

00:53:53.990 --> 00:53:57.050
Should we be trying to look,
once again, like those

00:53:57.050 --> 00:53:58.890
children in Burkina Faso?

00:53:58.890 --> 00:53:59.340
Probably.

00:53:59.340 --> 00:54:02.150
But it's going to be really hard
to get back there with

00:54:02.150 --> 00:54:04.060
our modern-day diets,
you know.

00:54:04.060 --> 00:54:06.170
And it doesn't matter how
many probiotics you

00:54:06.170 --> 00:54:07.290
dump into the system.

00:54:07.290 --> 00:54:10.740
That's just a living bacteria
that needs to be nourished in

00:54:10.740 --> 00:54:13.770
order for it to continue
to grow there.

00:54:13.770 --> 00:54:15.270
Does that makes sense?

00:54:15.270 --> 00:54:16.390
Thank you so much.

00:54:16.390 --> 00:54:21.080
[APPLAUSE]

